import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['precipitation'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Precipitation'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%b')

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data[data['month'] == month]['temp_max'] for month in data['month'].unique()], positions=range(1, 13), widths=0.6)
    ax.boxplot([data[data['month'] == month]['temp_min'] for month in data['month'].unique()], positions=range(1, 13), widths=0.6)
    
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['month'].unique())
    ax.set_xticks(range(1, 13))
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary throughout the year?')
    ax.legend(['Temp Max', 'Temp Min'], loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    weather_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Conditions')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
